article.description: Nick Smith went off for a career-high 30 points -- on 10 3-point baskets -- and Belmont steamrolled Tennessee-Martin 83-67 on Thursday night.
article.headline: Smith scores 30 on 10 3-pointers as Belmont tops UT Martin
article.linkText: Smith scores 30 on 10 3-pointers as Belmont tops UT Martin
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. -- Nick Smith went off for a career-high 30 points -- on 10 3-point baskets -- and Belmont steamrolled Tennessee-Martin 83-67 on Thursday night. Smith's 10 treys -- on 10-of 13-shooting -- also tied the Curb Event Center record for 3-pointers in a game. The Bruins (8-4, 2-0 Ohio Valley) shot 51 percent from the field (28 of 55) and were 18 for 35 from 3-point range -- one short of the school record. The rain of 3s began early as Amanze Egekeze hit one on Belmont's first possession for a 3-2 lead, which grew to 54-35 by halftime. Belmont's first six shots were from 3-pointer range. Egekeze finished with 11 points, Dylan Windler 15, and the Bruins had 22 assists on 28 made baskets. Jacolby Mobley led UT Martin (11-7, 1-2) with 22 points, Matthew Butler added 15 and Fatodd Lewis 14. Belmont and UT Martin were OVC division champions last season.
